This is not what it looks like! This mural by @pejac_art is called "Social Distancing" and it is a trompe l'oeil intervention that creates an illusion of a deep gaping crevice on a rigid surface of a cement wall. 
.
The artist says: "Made from countless human silhouettes that are trying to escape it, I wanted to represent the wound that this pandemic has left and do it as a tribute to health workers for their respect and solidarity towards the victims. While the image serves as a metaphor for the damage done by the pandemic, it also literally proposes Social Distancing as a way to fix them. In between the large crowd I included scenes of reunion, empathy, care, and love, suggesting a door to a better, hopeful future."
